=== Working Hours & New Flexibility Rules
While the 38-hour week remains the standard, new laws for 2026 introduce more flexibility:

- *Flexible Overtime:* The annual quota for flexible overtime has been extended to 360 hours for all workers, giving companies and employees more leeway during busy periods.
- *Remote & Hybrid Work:* Belgium is adapting to new ways of working. The government is promoting "teletrain work" (using commuter trains as mobile offices) and has introduced adjusted social security rules for digital nomads.

