=== Your Digital Handshake: Mastering LinkedIn
In the Belgian professional world, LinkedIn is your business card, resume, and network all in one. It is used very seriously.

*How to Optimise Your LinkedIn Profile:*
1.  *Professional Photo:* A clear, friendly, and professional headshot is non-negotiable.
2.  *Headline with Keywords:* Go beyond your job title. Include keywords for your industry and skills (e.g., "Senior Project Manager | Agile & Scrum | FinTech Innovation").
3.  *Detailed "About" Section:* Write a concise summary of your professional story, skills, and career goals.
4.  *Keep Experience Updated:* Recruiters and potential partners regularly check profiles for recent activity and detailed descriptions of your roles.
5.  *Personalise Connection Requests:* *Never* send a blank invitation. A short, polite note explaining who you are and why you want to connect makes all the difference. Example: _"Dear [Name], I enjoyed your presentation at the [Event Name] today. I'd like to connect to follow your work in [Industry]. Best regards, [Your Name]"_

